## Level 3 — Integration Errors (REST/SOAP)

### Error: REST call returns data but structure is empty
```
Symptom: API call succeeds (200) but response structure fields are all blank
Cause: JSON field names in response don't match structure attribute names (case-sensitive)

Debug:
  → Service Center / ODC Portal → Integration Log → view raw response JSON
  → Compare JSON keys to structure attribute names exactly

Fix:
  → Use "Name in JSON" property on structure attributes to map different names
  → Example: JSON returns "ticket_id" but attribute is "TicketId"
    → Set Name in JSON = "ticket_id"
```

### Error: SOAP SOAPFaultException
```
Symptom: SOAP call throws exception with fault code
Cause: External SOAP service returned a business or technical error

Fix:
  → Add specific exception handler for SOAPFaultException
  → Log fault code and fault message
  → Map to user-friendly error: "Payment processing failed. Code: " + FaultCode
  
  Exception handling code:
    Catch: SOAPFaultException
    Log: FaultCode + FaultMessage + Action inputs
    Raise UserException: "External service error: " + FaultMessage
```

### Error: REST timeout
```
Symptom: Integration call hangs then throws exception after 100 seconds
Cause: External service is slow, default timeout exceeded

Fix:
  → Set timeout property on REST method (in properties panel)
  → Add async pattern for long-running calls:
    1. Call external API to start job, get job ID
    2. Store job ID
    3. Use Timer to poll for completion
  → Show user a "Processing..." state in the meantime
```

### Error: WSDL import fails / SOAP structure changes
```
Symptom: After vendor updates their service, SOAP calls fail
Cause: WSDL schema changed — generated structures now mismatch

Fix:
  Step 1: Download new WSDL file from vendor
  Step 2: Re-import in Service Studio (Logic → SOAP → right-click → Refresh WSDL)
  Step 3: Fix any broken references (new/renamed parameters)
  Step 4: Republish and test
  → Wrapping SOAP calls in Service Actions means only the wrapper needs updating
```

