## Debugging Checklist (use for any error)

```
1. What layer is the error in?
   Screen → check widget visibility, input params, navigation
   Action → check logic flow, variable assignment, exception handlers
   Data → check aggregate filters, entity attributes, SQL syntax
   Integration → check request/response in Integration Log

2. Where exactly does it fail?
   → Add breakpoints progressively closer to the suspect area
   → Read the full error message and stack trace

3. What is the variable state at the point of failure?
   → Use Watch panel in Service Studio debugger
   → Or add LogMessage() to write variable values to General Log

4. Can I reproduce it consistently?
   → If yes → deterministic bug → trace back through logic
   → If no → intermittent → check for timing/concurrency or external dependency

5. Did something change recently?
   → New publish? → compare with previous version in Factory
   → External service change? → check Integration Log for different responses
   → Data volume increase? → performance-related

6. Check Service Center / ODC Portal logs FIRST before guessing
```
